	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Concerning the FDS-sound, this is something I actually emulated (well, sort of) in my old emulator A/NES for AmigaOS.<br />If the user inserted a 3.5&quot; floppy into the Amigadrive when booting an FDS-game, the reading sound was emulated by instead<br />reading the 3.5&quot; disk. I translated the byteoffset read into a sectoroffset and made the diskdrive make a &quot;dummyread&quot; just to get<br />a sound of the drive..

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


