		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Ha ha, I always hated when emulators for Amiga or Atari ST play a recording of the drive sound. I fondly remember the noise, but I don't find the recording really pushes the nostalgia button for me. It just sounds like a recording. Maybe if there was some sort of USB buzzing box I could attach... but this is not something I'd spend money on.<br /><br />Also I don't miss long load times and disk swapping at all. I usually fast forward the load bits anyway.

		

		</td>
